animal.description:
Jaxx the Lab Mix

This handsome boy is Jaxx, and he's in the market for his furever home. He is by all means a goofy, energetic lab with the sweetest smile and a glint in his eyes that could melt snow. He's a natural athlete that can clear a 6 foot fence and will run his own personal marathon were a door to be cracked open. Because he is quite the physical specimen, he needs to be on a lead even in a fenced in yard. Jaxx would do best in a low key environment with no young children. He has lived with other dogs before and currently has foster fur sibilings; however, he must be fed separately due to guarding behaviors. These same behaviors mean that he should never be allotted bones or treats that last longer than a chew or two. With some time and patience invested in trust-building and consistent training, he could be the new best friend you're looking for. If you're ready to welcome Jaxx into your life and head on over to OurBestFriendsRescue.org and fill out an application today.
Jaxx is approx 40 lbs and is 4 years old. 

Location: Greenwhich, NY
Adoption Fee: $400

animal.description:
Clous is a sweet senior soul.  He was found as a stray.  His owner was located.  However, for some reason, he did not wish to take Clous home.  How sad!  This boy deserves better.  

Clous is believed to be 11 years old and is a pit mix.  We think he is mixed with a Shar-pei.  Check out that cute wringly forehead!  Clous is a chill fella.  He walks well on a leash and rides well in the car.  He also sits for treats and takes them like a gentleman.  Clous loves neck scratches.  They are his favorite!   Clous is currently in foster with one of our volunteers.  She reports that is just the best boy!  He loves to go for walks and pays no mind to the cat.  

If you are interested in being his forever home, please visit our website, www.crcpa.org, and complete an application for Clous!  

Update:  Clous had a tumor removed.  He is healthy but the vet recommends a wellness check ups every three months.

animal.description: Greer is a young dog with the most adorable, squishy face. He looks like a cartoon character! Greer's favorite thing in the whole entire world is playing with stuffed toys. He'll carry them around in his mouth and leap in the air to catch them. Greer can be a little unsure when meeting new people, but given appropriate time and space, he adjusts quickly. Once he trust you, Greer enjoys being around people and even gets excited when you give him your attention and affection. Greer is a smart kiddo who learns quickly through force-free, science-based training methods. He would love to use his keen brain to solve food puzzles or learn new skills. Greer can be selective about his dog friends and would do best as the only dog in the home, or with a mature, neutral dog who will allow Greer time and space to get acclimated. Greer would do best with a family that has dog experience and is ready to commit to helping Greer be his best self! When Greer's needs are met, he's an absolute gem of a dog who is sure to bring laughter, joy, and love to your life.

Kid friendly: Older kids preferred

Jack is a very sweet boy! He will bond easily to whomever adopts him. He has shown interest in toys, and loves treats and responds to come and sit! He has shown a pretty high interest In people food and can easily get on counters, so we wouldn't suggest leaving food out. He has done well on walks so far, and was cooperative for his intake bath.

animal.description:
Shane is approximately four months of age.  He weighs under 30 lbs.  He will be arriving to AHR from our rescue partner in Louisiana, along with his brother Shawn.  

Like a typical four month old puppy, Shane is working on his training, leash skills, house and crate training.  

 We are looking for experienced families who are knowledgeable with this breed, who are willing to spend the time, money and energy to raise a well balanced dog who will be a good citizen. These puppies will not be adopted as first come first take, they will be placed appropriately

Adoption fees cover age specific vaccinations, spay/neuter, microchip, heartworm/lyme/ehrlichia test, worming and transport fees. 

Adoption fees: 
Through 6 months of age $450; 
7 months to through 5 years $400; 
6 years and under 9 years $325: bonded pairs are $500; 
9 years and older $250: bonded pairs are $300 

FOR PUPPIES: PLEASE READ!!
Homes considering Puppies must be prepared for:
Flexible Schedules for Potty Training. Puppies can only hold urine for one hour per month of age. Crate Training for the next 10 months to keep them safe from chewing on everything in your home. Supervision with Children and Obedience training. 
Socialization; both with new people, children and other dogs outside of the home.
Homes that want a well behaved dog, must be prepared to put the time, effort and costs associated to train a puppy. Well behaved dogs are not born, they are trained!  Please do not apply for a puppy if you cannot or do not have the time for a puppy.

Almost Home Rescue of New England is a 501 c 3 non-profit rescue; rescuing dogs since 2005. All Adoption applications are completed on line at www.almosthomerescue.net 

This dog is available unless it is marked as Pending, meaning Pending Adoption. This dog is in foster care locally, ONLY if Maine or New Hampshire is listed next to the dogs name; otherwise, the dog is still waiting with our partner rescue for an adoption or foster home in New England. 

PLEASE NOTE - We will check your veterinary reference, to ensure that current and prior dogs have a history of being kept up to date on rabies and distemper, have had annual heartworm tests, and are on heartworm preventative at least 6 months of the year. Current pets must by spayed/neutered. 

Imported dogs are transported on a USDA approved transport with a Health Certificate. All imported dogs are quarantined 14 days prior to getting on transport.

animal.description:
I had a rough start at life so I'm still learning to trust people. I like really like head and back rubs but need time and calm before I approach. I will calmly sit for an hour in your lap receiving pets but the first 10 minutes I'm going to be tense. I'm cautious but curious and want to trust again. I required hip surgery and the vet says I'm healing well. Even before the surgery the injury was not slowing me down any. I was happy to chase and tackle my 60lb friend but we had be supervised so I didn't get hurt. I'm a mature puppy. I love to play with toys independently but I'm still learning what is approved for me to play with. I'm learning to walk on a leash. I love that it lets me explore safely but as soon as I feel a little tug I freak out some. My foster mom thinks I'm overly dramatic in these situations but I'm just trying to make sure I'm safe and not hurt. I look forward to having a forever home and I'm willing to share affection with other pets. My adoption fee is $250 Houston area
(Available for transport $550, includes adoption fee, health certificate, and transportation)
and includes all my vaccinations, microchip, and neuter. I also tested heartworm negative. Fill out an app at www.soca-fbc.org under the adoptable tab.

animal.description: Hi! My name is Indie AKA Lightning. I was rescued by Big Dog Ranch Rescue while wandering around the Miami Dolphins stadium with a fellow stray pup. I am a very sweet and cuddly dog who loves to snuggle up in bed with the people that I love. I also love to be outside and go for long walks or runs! I love people, including young children, and am always super friendly when I meet new friends. I get along well with other dogs and animals as long as we are in situations in which there is no food present. So I may be the type of pup that you can bring out and about to socialize with other dogs, but I should always remain the only dog in the home to avoid any bad interactions due to food aggressiveness. I have never lived with a feline companion but I do appear to be fearful of them and would ask that any possible introductions be done very gradually. I am well-trained, including potty-trained, and know a few important commands. I'm not one to bark much and I've never been known to be a chewer either. I'm really a very sweet dog that just needs to be the queen of my own castle!

Dutch is a 8 month old, neutered, pittie mix that we rescued from a local town shelter. He has a rough start to his life but is now safe with us. Dutch is a fun loving and sweet boy. He is an extremely active dog who would love hiking, agility or romps around a fenced yard. Dutch spent the majority of his short life in the shelter system so he would greatly benefit from a home that is willing to provide structure, training, exercise and of course lot's of love! He would do best with an experienced dog owner. Although, he has gotten along with most dogs, we do recommend him being the only pet. 
Dutch is an awesome pup who has great potential!

animal.description: May and her sister, April, both came to Pasadena Humane as strays. While May is an absolute beauty of a German Shepherd, her personality so far has been hard to analyze. May looks to her sister for clues on what to do, so obviously April is more confident in whatever is happening. May remains scared and confused so our staff has been working to try to convince her that everything is okay. But in her mind, it's not okay and she is watchful from the back of her kennel. A great deal of patience is going to be needed to help her relax. But by looking at the most recent picture of her, you can easily see a pretty relaxed dog standing in our play yard! Recently volunteers have reported that May is much braver when April is around and then May will wag her tail and allow some petting. As time goes by, we will update our progress with what we know can be a sweet dog! Learn more about our virtual adoption process .

animal.description:
All dogs adopted through Troy Animal Rescue Project will be up to date on vaccinations, spayed/neutered (age appropriate), and heartworm negative before adoption. All dogs are given monthly flea/tick preventative, monthly heartworm preventative, and are dewormed regularly. Dogs adopted through Troy Animal Rescue Project are microchipped. Adoption fee is $50. Home visit and vet reference required. Applications can be put in online at http://www.troyanimalrescueproject.org/adopt.php or in person at our rescue center. ***WE DO NOT DO SAME DAY ADOPTIONS***

The address for our rescue center is 34 County Road 2266, Brundidge, AL 36010. We are one turn off Hwy 167. If you use Google maps, type in Troy Animal Rescue Project and it will take you right to us. Hours of operation are from 11-3 daily. We are open Saturdays and Sundays. No appointment necessary for pets that are located at the rescue center. Appointments must be made to visit pets in foster homes. Appointments can be made by calling 334-508-2367 or emailing troyanimalrescueproject@gmail.com. Location information will be listed beside the pets name if they are at a location other than our rescue center.

Questions can be emailed to troyanimalrescueproject@gmail.com or call 334-508-2367.

animal.description:
Meet Cairo. She was rescued from a kill shelter and placed in a foster home. In the few short weeks she has been there, this girl has been nothing short of amazing. She is so insanely sweet, gets along great with other dogs, is good with the cat, walks on a leash, is house broken and crate trained. She hung out with a little 2 year old boy and she seemed to enjoy him. She is still learning how to be a carefree dog but is making great progress. She is very shy and will melt into the floor when approached in hopes the person will be kind and loving to her. She is a big time snuggle bug and is happy to be cuddled up on the couch with her human or a furry friend. She is so insanely sweet and loving that its hard for her foster humans to believe someone ever let this sweet pup end up at the kill shelter. Because she is so shy, it would be best for her to be in a home with another dog that can continue to show her how to be a dog. She would also benefit from a home with a fenced in yard or a more active lifestyle as she loves to go for walks and runs.

animal.description:
Meet Memphis! Memphis is a 1 year old Pit bull mix. He has a winning personality. He is a well-mannered, affectionate boy. He loves getting back scratches and being loved on. He is a loyal, friendly, smart boy. Memphis has done well with other dogs his size, and older kids. A fenced in yard is preferred for Memphis. If you would like to make Memphis a part of your family, please fill out an adoption application at www.barktownrescue.org

Adoption Fee: $170

*Due to Covid 19 restrictions some of our new intakes vet scheduling has been delayed. We will still go ahead and schedule your meet and greet even if all the vetting needed has not been completed. Once vetting is complete the approved adopter will be able to take their dog/cat home to their forever home.The shelter software system requires that we choose a predominant breed or breed mix for our dogs. Visual breed identification in dogs is unreliable so for most of our dogs we are only guessing at the dog's predominant breed or breed mix. We strongly encourage you to select your new pet by looking at each dog's individual personality and pet qualities rather than relying on a breed label that is only our best guess.

Our adoption fees vary from $150 and up. All of our dogs are up to date on vaccines, heart worm preventives, and flea/tick medication, and will be spayed/neutered prior to adoption. Portions of your adoption fee also help care for the sick and injured animals that we take in. Thank you for supporting us and considering a rescue dog!

animal.description:
Senior Hearts Rescue and Renewal is the only licensed senior dog rescue organization in Western Pennsylvania. We do not have a shelter or a public facility. ALL of our dogs reside in foster homes in the greater Pittsburgh, PA area. 

We are a 100% volunteer organization. Please respect our volunteers' time. If a dog is listed on PetFinder, he/she IS available for adoption. We cannot reply to messages, phone calls, and emails about a dog until we have received, reviewed, and approved an adoption application. 

Our ADOPTION application is found at www.seniorhearts.org Completing this application is the first step in our adoption screening process. You MUST complete the application in its entirety in order to be considered as a potential adopter.  Please select "More About Us" for further details on our adoption requirements.  You can meet a dog ONLY after we have completed our adoption approval process.

If you are looking at the dog below, it most certainly means the dog is available for adoption. We look forward to receiving your application in hopes that you are able to meet our adoption requirements and provide this dog with a loving furever home.

Good evening world! My name is Cleo and I have just begun a search for my furever family.  I am a 12-year-old beagle and weigh 24 pounds.  I am a pretty chill kinda girl.  I love going for walks and sniffing everything so sometimes we don't get too far because of my darn nose.  It would be awesome to have a backyard so I could sniff away.

I am very friendly and get along with all dogs cats and humans.  I am an easy-going companion that is happy as can be hanging next to my human and watching Netflix.  A dog sibling would be great but definitely not needed for me.  

If we end up together I promise all the unconditional love you can handle. I can be adopted within a two-hour radius of Pittsburgh, PA. If you are interested in giving me a furever home, you must first complete the adoption application at www.seniorhearts.org

animal.description:
My name is Sarah, I have been bounced around and am looking for a forever home.  I need a home that has a great understanding of the husky breed.  I moved from CA to WA about a year ago.  I am 5 years old, but have tons of energy and act like I am one. 
I love to play and run all day long. I get so excited that I forgot my manners and will accidentally run you over. 
I am also not your average husky. I am a husky mix, most likely with malamute which makes me a 60-70 lb dog. I have very pretty long hair but I am stubborn about being brushed. It feels so good after a couple swipes. I have to go run and snort. Oh yeah I make lots of funny noises and guarantee will make you laugh. 
I need a home with a good secured fenced yard where I can run. My rescuers are asking for no small children due to my manners aren't the greatest. Absolutely NO small animals. I don't know what it is about them but I don't like them. They are funny looking to me. 
I need someone that can take me on regular walks and spend time with me and help me work on my manners. My foster mom has helped me greatly but there is still room for improvement. I would really like to be the only dog but I might accept a nice male dog that is around my size and age and can play just as hard as I do."  Please contact nwsnowdogrescue@aol.com

animal.description: Meet medium size and medium energy Brock who would love a serene and calm place to retire.  Brock was adopted over 6 years ago after he was rescued by RCR and transported from a high kill shelter in Georgia to Washington state.  Sadly, now 8-year-old Brock is again looking for his forever home as his owner of 6 years has a new girlfriend who doesn’t like Brock.  Jack Russell mix Brock is back with his former foster in Moses Lake while he awaits a patient and loving adopter who has no other pets or children. Brock weighs just 28lbs and is still as active and playful as he was years ago. He’s had a lot of changes lately, so Brock needs an adopter who is knowledgeable about fearful dogs and who is willing to give him time to adjust. Brock is skittish and reactive to loud noises and sudden moves. He likes daily walks and needs an enclosed, fenced in yard. Brock is a pretty calm boy once he feels comfortable with you and will gladly be a couch potato with you or more likely your lap warmer. If you give him the ability and space to choose the amount and type of interaction he wants, he thrives!  Brock craves attention and loves to snuggle. He would love to be with a single person who is without kids and is not away from home for too many hours a day.  Brock is totally house trained and crate-trained. He gets along well with other dogs after proper intros, but really just prefers being with you, his people! Brock happily sleeps and hangs out in his crate.  Brock is very food motivated and is very smart.  He knows his basic commands and sits before going in a door and on command. He is also quite good with “stay” and will give you his “paw”. Brock LOVES squeaker toys! Loud and sudden noises seem to remind him of his past and startle him which makes us assume it wasn't a very happy past. This is Brock’s last chance at finding an experienced and caring adopter who can make Brock the center of their world. We are hoping that we can find Brock a home that will guarantee him a happy future. Brock's adoption fee is $150 and he is neutered, micro-chipped and fully-vaccinated.  For questions and a conversation with his foster mom Lindsey, please email rcrlindsey@gmail.com. Brock is currently being fostered in Moses Lake, WA. To complete an application, go to www.raincityrescue.com/adopt.  Best boy Brock might be a bit complicated, but if you need a project and to help save a life- Brock will be totally worth your time to check out.  He will repay you with kisses and loves and gratitude forever!

animal.description:
Macallister (“Mac”) is an approx. 2-4 year old Pibble who LOVES life. He’s a fun, loving dog who enjoys playing with his toys, running around the yard, exploring, and going for walks. As much as Mac appreciates playtime and keeping active, he enjoys relaxing just as much once it’s time to do so.

Here’s Mac in a nutshell…

He’s a sensitive guy who wears his heart on his sleeve. He LOVES being around his people!
About 45 pounds and 2-4 years old
Loves to run around and would enjoy a yard in his new home, although this is not a requirement
Very active but also likes to chill when it’s time to do so. He can be your adventure and cuddle buddy all in one!
Does well with other dogs and has a rough play style. Mac would likely do fine with another dog in the home who could match his playstyle, but he would also love to be your one & only and we would prefer that for him, too!
Foster dad describes him as a truly special guy who makes a fantastic companion with his great personality and his sense of humor. 


Mac is updated on all vaccinations, neutered, and microchipped. If you are interested in adding this darling boy to your crew, please fill out an adoption application at https://form.jotform.com/92017020417141 or send us an email at noarcfosteradopt@gmail.com with any questions. Mac can’t wait to meet you!

For information on how our adoption process works, please visit our website at www.thenoarc.com

Please note: prospective adopters must be located within the state of Ohio OR within 3 hours of Columbus, Ohio.

Also note that while we welcome questions from prospective adopters, it is much easier for us to fully answer questions and provide guidance if an adoption application has been filled out.

**If this posting is up, Mac is still available for adoption :)**

animal.description: Hello everyone! Abby here. I'm a 3-legged firecracker with an independent spirit packed into my 8 lb body.  At 9 years young, I am full of life, and while I do need help with stairs or to get in your lap for a quick snuggle, I can hold my own. My vision and hearing are slipping a bit so please make sure that any stairs are safeguarded. When you’re in the kitchen cooking, I like to try and trip you up, so watch your step — I gotta be where the action is, after all! My favorite pastime is sleeping in the dog beds and trust me, I've got this down to a science. My foster dad takes me outside every time I wake up, and I do my business with efficiency and am ready to get back inside. My potty habits are a work in progress so please be patient with me. I'm a really sweet gal that just wants to be pampered throughout my golden years. I'm quiet and don’t need a lot of space so either a home or apartment will suit me just fine. I have been diagnosed with bronchial malacia, my bronchial tubes coming off my esophagus are narrow and deformed causing me to cough. We are trying different medications to see what will work best for me, but I may need to be on medication the rest of my life. If you are ready to welcome a sleeping beauty into your home, fill out an application. Abby is spayed, up to date on all vaccines, had a heart worm test, on heartworm preventative, had a fecal, a dental, and microchipped. Abby’s adoption fee is $275.00.

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Samson! I am an 8 yr old, 12 lb Chihuahua.

- A little backstory...my sweet mama got Alzheimer's and was unable to care for me so our neighbor did everything she could to find me a new home but ended up taking me to the shelter where the lovely HIT Wives rescued me!

- I am a GEM of a boy. I can be a little shy at first, but just wants to be loved and I will jump in people’s laps for affection within about three minutes of meeting them! 

- I am a very easy, low maintenance boy to have. I don't chew nor dig, I take treats gently, and don't ever beg. I am a really sweet boy, good with everyone, who needs to be cherished and loved. 

- I am generally a medium energy dog. I don't need a lot of activity, but I do love my walks!

- Sitting on laps is my favorite. So much so that I often fall asleep there :) Who doesn't love cuddling? 

- I am good with other dogs, am FULLY house trained, and just had a bunch'o teeth removed so give me all of the soft and yummy treats please!

- I always want to be with you! Separation anxiety is something I'm learning to work through and already getting much better, and I will need a patient individual or family to help me overcome it and not feel like I am getting abandoned every time you leave. My foster mom is helping me lots and says that now when she leaves she hears me bark for a little, and then I stop and go settle down. 

- I am ready for my forever home and to get alllll the love I deserve!!! 

If you see me online I am still available for adoption! If you are interested in adopting me please fill out an application here: www.hitlivingfoundation.org/adoption-application, and email a video walkthrough of your home and yard to BOTH Nicole@hitlivingfoundation.org AND Marta@hitlivingfoundation.org. Your application will not be counted as valid without your video. You will hear back from us within a few days.

animal.description:
ADOPTION OF A PUPPY UNDER 9 MONTHS OF AGE

The dog you are interested in is a puppy (under a year old). We have criteria for our adoptions of puppies. Puppies are adopted on a foster-to-adopt basis until the puppy is old enough to be neutered/spayed (we prefer them to be no younger than 7 months for females and 9 months for males). Houses with pools must demonstrate that puppies can be protected from the pool with fencing or a cover. Home visits for shots will be required, so puppies are adopted to homes in Maricopa County only. Puppies often have multiple potential adopters, so SPR evaluates what home is best matched with any given puppy and their expected home needs once they have grown.

Lucy is an energetic puppy that loves everyone. She gets along with other dogs and kids, but is still learning not to jump, so she will need a family willing to help keep training her. She is a fast learner and is already potty trained and knows sit, lay down, and stay. Even though her knickname is the mini Mal, due to her petite size, she loves playing with her bigger foster brothers and smaller foster sister. We recommend that she goes to a home with another dog to play with.. She’s ready for a loving forever home!


If you can give Lucy  an indoor forever home, please fill out our online application on our website at http://www.savingpawsrescueaz.com/adoption-form/  

 We will only schedule meet and greets with an approved application. We are an all-volunteer organization.  It may take a couple of days to process an application and complete reference checks.

Thank you for your interest in saving the life of a puppy and providing for it's FOREVER home.

animal.description:
Buster is such a fantastic pup! We first lay eyes on him when the NYC shelter sent out a plea to save his life. We saw his picture and had no idea what kind of dog he was. He was a big mass of black matted fur and kind of looked like he would be a fluffy type of pup. To our amazement, once the matted fur was shaved off, there stood the cutest little chubby Scottish Terrier!!!!! 
This poor little boy had been so neglected and on top of barely being able to move his head without pain from the mats, he had horrible ear infections. We’ve had them treated and he’s starting to feel much better now. We will have them rechecked around January 11th to make sure he’s doing well. We got him too late to help his one ear that had a hematoma at some time but the other ear is pure Scottie. 
Buster is a little love bug who wants nothing more than a lap and lots of love. He does need to have his food monitored as he is a chow hound and will eat until he explodes if you let him. He is a small Scottie but at 15lbs is still in need of losing about 2lbs. 
Buster is afraid of leash walking but is getting better with a little practice. He’s great on car rides and is really very easy going. 
If you’re looking for a sweet little man to spend your time with, he’s your guy! 
Buster is located in Freeport NY
His adoption fee is $550
We do not have any way to cat test our pups. Please do not ask! If other animals are in a prospective adoptive home a meet and greet must be done. Applications do not guarantee you will get the dog you are applying for. 
Please be patient after you’ve sent in an app on a dog. This is an all-volunteer organization, everyone works and has families. This is done in our not so spare time.

AVAILABLE FOR A LOVING FAMILY!!

Licorice is a 13 lb, 15 month old male Terrier mix ready for his forever family.
Licorice is good with other friendly dogs, and humans, but would do best in a home with no small children. He's smart, agile, a very quick learner, and like most small Terriers, he needs a confident human that understands the Terrier breed so that he doesn't have to take charge.
Licorice would love to hike or go with his human biking, and needs at least a long walk daily. He is house trained, crate trained and good on the leash. Licorice would excel at agility training and loves to learn and please. He'd love another dog to play with too!
His adoption fee is $250.00 and includes his neuter, current vaccinations and microchip. For profile with an adoption application, visit https://spotsavespets.org/dogs-n-puppies/

animal.description:
Bluetick Coonhounds can be wonderful companions and great family dogs when properly trained and socialized.  Coonhounds can have loud voices and are not typically suited for apartments, condominium or city living. Coonhounds make excellent family pets. They are good with children of all ages and usually take all the petting that is dished out.

MEET BILLY.  He's around two years old and it was evident he had not been cared for when we got him.  Billy found himself homeless when his family moved and left him behind.  When we learned of his need for rescue we opened out hearts to this handsome boy knowing he was going to need medical attention.  Both eyes needed surgery for cherry eye plus he's heart worm positive.

Currently at our vets office being medically cared for, Billy will be ready for a home by the middle of February.  In the mean time we are working on applications to find his home as soon as possible.

Our medical care for all rescues is: 
DHLPP vaccines, Rabies vaccine, Influenza vaccine, Lyme vaccine.  4dx snap test to check-The test is a screening process for six vector-borne diseases. We are checking your dog for Heartworm, Lyme, Ehrlichia canis, Ehrlichia ewingi, Anaplasma phagocytophilum and Anaplasma platys.  Spay or neuter if at least six months old.  heart worm and flea preventative, fecal test and treatment, basic exam and treatment as needed.

animal.description: My name is Kai. I am about 4-5 years old. I was rescued from an overcrowded shelter. I have a few things I am currently working through but who isn't! I don't always have the best manners when I meet other dogs or people. I try really hard but I just get so excited to play that I forget to introduce myself properly. I definitely like to be super active...like all day! No lazy dog here! Don't get me wrong, I will snuggle and cuddle and I don't shed bad, but I want to be where the action is! I do like having alot of attention also!  I am probably not good around small kids. I can get along with other dogs, but it has to be an extremely laid back dog or a super active one that can try and keep up with me. I can be a little hard headed, but that's because I've been on my own for a while now. I am really ready to have a big yard of my own and people who are patient with me as I work on my manners. I love to fetch and run and play games! I am super smart and can find my treats in those silly games my foster humans got for me! I'm ready for a real challenge!

animal.description:
The Beagle personality is marked by a bold and cheerful disposition.  They are avid working dogs that combine intense drive and cuddly good looks into an adorable package.

These curious dogs take in their environment through their nose, and they’re often found scenting as if magnetized to the ground. This natural tendency to sniff can make it challenging to keep a Beagle’s attention, and if a scent is too tempting to resist, many Beagles are prone to take off without a backward glance. For this reason, it’s suggested that Beagles only be off leash in fenced areas.

Because of their friendly attitude Beagles are good family dogs. They’re cheerful and clever and can be a fantastic match for families that are able to meet their exercise needs. Beagles are generally very good with kids who understand how to interact with and handle dogs.

MEET OUR BEAGLE- RICKY!   Around four years old, Ricky found himself in a shelter in South Carolina for three months with no one wanting him.  We believe this is because hounds in the southern shelters are plentiful AND because he was heart worm positive.   The cost to treat can easily deter an adopter.  So, lucky for Ricky Di fell in love with him and, as a holiday present, he was her rescued dog that she vetted and shared with our rescue to re-home.

He has not been fully vetted and is available for adoption.  Although currently in NC at our vets office, we will transport to an approved adopter.  You can find an online application on our webpage, http://diamonddogsrescueinc.com

animal.description:
Kobi and his companion Bella were found exploring the neighborhood after their fencing fell down.

When their owner was contacted, they stated they couldn’t afford to pay the fees to get them out of the shelter, so they abandoned them there.

Bella had healing wounds around her neck, most likely from being chained or tethered.  Both were underweight and in rough shape though Kobi seems to have fared better physically.

We are having Bella examined by our vet before she's made available.

Despite the neglect they endured, both of them are overflowing with love and affection, which they seemed to have been deprived of.  

Kobi is just a youngster at approx 1 year old with a whole lot of growing to do!  He’s a already a big, strong boy with an unbridled sense of adventure.

He fires on all cylinders and is eager to get out and see the world.  We can’t blame him for his enthusiasm, if he’s been isolated in a yard his whole life.

He could be mixed with German Shepherd or a combination of other breeds, but nonetheless he’s a friendly, outgoing, lover.  He enjoys meeting new people and doesn’t know the meaning of “aloof”!  To the contrary, he can be a bit overzealous when greeting people so will need to learn proper etiquette!

Kobi will be enrolled in a basic obedience and manners class before he’s available, so he can be the best he can be!  His new owner will need to continue implementing his training and socialization as part of his daily routine as he matures and grows.

His ideal guardian is someone who is active and maybe even likes to run and hike.  You should be an experienced large breed individual who is familiar with setting boundaries and maintaining rules.

Kobi will require a home with a large fenced yard.  No apartments or townhouses will be considered. 

No children in his future home as he is much too big and energetic for little humans.

It might be the mix in him, as Kobi is not a typical Akita and seems to be quite social with many other well mannered dogs his size.  He may do well with an appropriately matched female of equal activity level.

Check back for updates as we get better acquainted with Kobi. 

If you are interested in adopting, please complete our adoption application found on our website here:  https://www.namasteakitarescue.com/how-do-i-adopt

There you will find helpful information about the adoption process, FAQ's, etc


**PLEASE NOTE, we must first approve an application before a meeting can be arranged between a prospective adopter and our dogs.

Please email us for additional information or if you have questions: info@namasteakitarescue.com

animal.description:
Daisee is a 3 year old spayed female pit bull/bulldog mix who weighs about 50 lbs. Daisee was rescued from a high kill shelter after being found as a stray with a horrible leg injury. Despite the pain and discomfort she must have been in, Daisee has been an absolute sweetheart from the moment we met her. She has been receiving treatment for her leg and has been a wonderful patient. She seems to be so thankful for all the attention and care we've been giving her. This girl has the most beautiful blue brindle coat that feels like velvet. She loves to be with her people and spending time outside. Daisee is still working on her training and will need an experienced and dedicated family that will be consistent and provide positive reinforcement so she can continue to learn and grow. She doesn't seem comfortable around children, so she will need a home without them. Daisee loves to play, but has a medium energy level overall. She's done well with dogs she has met, and even seemed okay with cats. After everything she's been through, Daisee is so deserving of an amazing home that will give her all the love and attention she wants. She is sure to repay the favor ten-fold! Please help us find Daisee the forever family she is dreaming of!

Interested in adopting? Take the first step and complete an adoption application on our website: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/
We are a foster based organization, so we do not have a facility to visit. Please read our FAQs to learn more: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/faq
Follow us on Facebook for foster updates and a full list of our adoptable pets: https://www.facebook.com/all4pawsrescue/

As I was a street dog most of my live, not many people have been nice to me, and I’ve had to scrounge around for food. Therefore, I do have some trust issues and am wary of strangers. I am better with women. However, once you win me over, I am a big cuddle bug and will be forever loyal to you! Furthermore, due to my time on the streets, I would not like humans or animals to disturb me while I am eating. It is best to separate me while I am eating and let me be alone. I am currently at a wonderful lady’s house who is training me to mind my space and focus on my leader. I love treats and cuddles. I realize I am not as easy as some other dogs. However, if you give me a chance, with the right person, I will be the most loyal and happy lap dog.

animal.description:
Snow
1.5 yr old lab/shepherd mix

Snow came from Nemaska, Quebec with her six puppies through IFAW’s Northern Dog Project. She was a great mama to all of her babies. Now that they’ve all been adopted, it’s time for her to find a forever family of her own.
Snow needed time to warm up to the resident dogs in her foster family as she was initially protective of her puppies, but once she realized they posed no threat she allowed them into her social bubble and even accepted their help raising her puppies. They are now best of friends. She plays very well with the male dog and follows the rules set out by the senior small dog in her foster home. She likes to be close to her humans and especially likes to rest her head in your lap and snuggle up close. Snow LOVES to play ball. She is incredibly agile and driven. She is a great jumper so a secure fence is important, but she prefers to go on walks to take care of her business so a backyard is not essential for her. She has a strong prey drive towards squirrels and rabbits while on walks, but responds well to redirection with verbal cues and treats. Due to lockdown restrictions, we have been unable to test her with cats.
Snow would do best with another active, playful dog in the home. She will otherwise require a very active human who will take her on long walks, hikes, and runs to make sure she has an opportunity to drain her energy and to keep her body and mind active. She has been very good with the people she has met since coming into foster care, but her interactions have been limited due to lockdown. She is working on basic obedience and manners in her foster home. Adolescent obedience classes would be beneficial for her and her new family. Snow is house-trained and crate-trained, but has been free roaming in her foster home since her puppies were weaned.

Snow has been a lovely addition to her foster family. She fits in well with everyone and is eager to please. If you’re looking for a smart, loyal, and affectionate sidekick, Snow would love to meet you! 

Snow has been vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, spayed, heartworm tested and treated with Advantage Multi

The adoption fee is $600 and includes spay/neuter (dogs over 6 months), vaccines, heartworm test (dogs over 6 months), deworming, Flea and tick prevention and microchip. Please visit www.paws-united.com to fill out an application.
**For puppies under 6 months a $200 spay/neuter rebate will be given with proof of spay/neuter certificate signed by a vet, if they have not been done prior to adoption.**
**Please note we DO NOT adopt our dogs as outdoor/farm dogs. These dogs are coming to us as stray, roaming or dogs that have lived a life tied to a chain. Our goal is to bring them in the house off the chain and give them a pampered indoor dogs lifestyle. Unless otherwise stated we will not even consider a home that has intentions of leaving our dogs outdoors or tied to a chain**

Bio:
Hello, my name is Meyli! It means “beautiful”, which, if I do say so myself, suits me perfectly! I’m an independent lady, who likes doing her own thing. I enjoy being in the presence of people, but I won’t beg for attention. I’m not a fan of cuddling. I’m a bit skittish, so for that reason I cannot go to a home with young children. I might do better with older kids who can understand that I like having my space. I’m not very energetic, but I do love playing with toys. I like chasing balls and swinging around a rope toy. Once I’ve gotten my playtime in, I enjoy just lying around and relaxing. I need help learning to walk nicely on leash so I need a proper harness and some training. I don't like bunnies in my yard, so if you adopt me, please bunny-proof your yard! If I sound like the girl for you, please ask about me today!

Leash: Needs work
Obedience: Knows basic skills like sit, stay, lie down!
Containment: A fenced in yard
With other Dogs: Unknown
With cats: Unknown
With small children: Not suitable

Adoption comes with:

* Mandatory spaying/neutering
* First license
* Veterinarian check-up
* First vaccinations
* Tattoo
* Microchip implant
* 6 weeks of free pet insurance
* Small bag of dog food
* De-worming for young pups
 * Literature on responsible pet ownership.

------------------------------------

** IMPORTANT NOTICE **
Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, dog adoptions are currently being done by appointment only. Contact 311 to schedule an appointment. Thank you!

______________________________

Come Meet Our Adoptable Dogs...
Winnipeg Animal Services Agency
1057 Logan Avenue
Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada
R3E 3N8

Phone: 311 - outside Winnipeg dial 1-877-311-4974 

Email: animalservicesagency@winnipeg.ca

Our hours for adoption are Monday to Friday from 11:00 am - 5:30 pm
Saturday & Sunday from 12:00 pm - 4:30pm.
Animal Services is closed on statutory holidays.

BACKGROUND
Almost all the dogs at Animal Services are picked up as strays running loose on the streets of Winnipeg and therefore they come to us with no known history. For this reason, we are not sure how they will interact with other dogs, cats or how they are with children. We would suggest that if you have younger children you bring them down with you to meet the dogs. We also have an outdoor play area where we can do introductions with any other dogs that live in the home.

All locally adopted dogs come with a 7 day home trial. If you return the dog within this time period, you will be refunded your adoption fee less the non-refundable deposit.

Please feel free to meet all the dogs and puppies outside of their kennels, just let the kennel attendants know that you would like a meet and greet with the dog outside of his pen. The dogs are much more relaxed when outside of their kennels. They would love to meet you!

animal.description:
Judy was surrendered by her family along with an adult male and their four puppies... where they were living outdoors. She was a good mom but after they got big enough she was more than happy to detach herself from them haha. We have spent the last few weeks getting to know her and learn the best home environment for her. She is a very happy and very playful girl.. she loves to chew on bones, chase toys, and love on people. Judy is 2 years old but is still learning appropriate behaviors since she never lived indoors before. She would strongly benefit from a home willing to put time into her training by continuing to use positive reinforcement training that she is thriving with. 
At this time we are suggesting a home with no toddler age or younger children, as well as no other animals. She is a very bossy female and since she grew up with the male dog she was surrendered with, he seems to tolerate it for the most part.

Judy is a pint sized girl at 32lbs and a very petite stature.. her ears are probably the biggest thing about her and they can hear treat bags open from two rooms away - so Beware! :) She is fully vetted, fixed and has no medical issues to note.

Adoption Process: PLEASE READ!
Judy has a $300 adoption fee.
Anyone interested in meeting our adoptables must complete an online application, which is located on our website. This site is updated weekly so if an animal is listed they are available for adoption. Once the application is approved we will set up a meet and greet with the animal to ensure a good fit and then before adoption is complete we will schedule a home check to ensure a safe environment for the animal you are looking to adopt. If you live outside of the Tri-County area we will do our best to accommodate a home visit but it will rely on the availability and volunteers at that time. At this time we cannot do out of the state adoptions. We also do not do on-the-spot adoptions and we do not adopt out animals by a first-come, first-serve basis. We strive to fit everyone of our animals to the best match possible! We pride ourselves in responsibly placing animals in homes that are best fit for their needs.

If you are looking for a gentle senior who wants to give and receive love, Maggie is the one for you! She is calm and sweet and content to stay right with her people. She walks nicely on her leash, taking her time and checking out the yard or the block. She has gotten along well with everyone she’s met and shares nicely with the other pets in her foster home, drinking from the communal water dish and curling up together on the blanket for naps.

Maggie does need frequent potty breaks, so she would do best in a home where someone can take her out every couple of hours. She is happy to use her crate at night or for shorter daytime naps. Her ideal Forever Home would be a quieter one. Though she is friendly with visitors, she is an older lady who would not be up to the activity level of young children. And although she has gotten along fine with her foster brother, she needs a lot of individual attention and would be fine as an only dog or possibly in a household with one other easygoing, older dog.

animal.description:
After being abandoned, Archie found his way to the home of a family who took him in to care for him while they searched for rescue.   He was not in very good shape, with a severe ear infection, a cough and heart worms.  Once we learned about him and his very sweet personality we were anxious to get him into our vets office where she could begin to treat him medically.  Currently he is in North Carolina and we are expecting that by the end of January he will be ready to find a home.  This time, one that will care for him!

Archie is thought to be around 2 years old and a beagle mix.  He is such a sweet affectionate dog.  Loves his person and looks to please.  Because Beagles have traditionally been raised in large packs, they do not do well as a single pet, left alone all day. Their frustration will quickly lead to excessive barking and destructive behavior. A second dog for companionship is strongly recommended.

Our basic medical is as follows:  DHLPP vaccines, Rabies vaccine, Influenza vaccine, Lyme vaccine.  4dx snap test to check-The test is a screening process for six vector-borne diseases. We are checking your dog for Heartworm, Lyme, Ehrlichia canis, Ehrlichia ewingi, Anaplasma phagocytophilum and Anaplasma platys.  Spay or neuter if at least six months old.  heart worm and flea preventative, fecal test and treatment, basic exam and treatment as needed.

animal.description:
Hi there!  My name is SHILOH.  What’s yours?  Nice to meet ya!  I am in Houston, TX.  If you live nearby or within driving distance, can you come to pick me up to go home with you?

A nice person came along and took me in and, now, I am ready to hit the road to your house!  Uh, make that “our” house, OK?  I definitely need a house with a fenced-in yard cuz I need room to run and romp and be safe!  The rescue requires (1) a fenced-in yard and (2) a vet reference from a vet that you have used for a current or previous dog to be sure that all vetting was done.  

I am a Corgi/Beagle mix, we think.  I am 5-years old and I weigh 20 pounds.  I have been neutered and am up to date on vaccines so I'm ready to go to my new home with YOU!!  Those funny-looking 2-legged creatures said I’m also microchipped – whatever THAT is.  At any rate, I am fully vetted.  Is that anything close to petted?  I love to be petted!  They say I'm precious.  Hmmm, Is my name Shiloh or Precious?

Wanna hear some more good stuff about me?  OK, here goes.  I like ALL people and dogs.  I am sweet and playful.  I haven't been around children and I might very well be OK with them but let's hope for a home with just adults.  OK?

I need my own home.  I'm still young enough to have a good, long life with you taking care of me and I'll take care of YOU!

Since I was rescued, I've learned to use a doggie door at my foster's home.  Smart, huh? I like to take naps when I'm tired from playing.  I need  love, exercise and couch-sitting when we get tired!  Let's be a team, OK?

If you would like to take me home (and you know you do), please email doggydarlings12@gmail.com  and they can get me on my way to a new and loving home!  My adoption fee is $150 and includes my vetting, neutering, and a microchip.

animal.description:
BAXTER

Baxter is a big, big boy with a huge heart and love for people. Baxter is about 4 years old and 66 pounds. He should probably weigh closer to 80.  

Baxter seems to have lived a life without much care. He was emaciated and very fearful when we first brought him into Lone Star. He has turned around completely with lots of love, good food and structure. Now he is happy in his big kennel and his fearfulness is almost gone.  Baxter has learned that people are kind and caring, so there is nothing to worry about. He LOVES to jump up and "give hugs" to his people, that can knock you over if you are not watching!
 
Baxter will do best in an active, adult home with a fenced yard. He is house trained and crate trained, too. Because of his history of fearfulness, he will be better in a home without young children. We are looking for a new owner who has experience with large dogs.

Baxter is vaccinated, neutered and microchipped. He will have heartworm treatment in January and be ready for adoption in February.

You are welcome to complete an adoption application for Baxter now, if you live in the DFW area. See our web site for information on our adoption process. Baxter's adoption fee is $295 + tax.  www.LoneStarLabRescue.org

animal.description:
Benjamin is our beautiful work in progress!  Police dropped Ben off at a Philadelphia shelter after he was found injured and suffering from an awful skin condition.  He fully recovered in his foster home and has turned into a stunning boy.  At two years old he is full of life and loves to play.   In the evening he loves nothing more than to sprawl on the sofa with you and snuggle until bedtime. He sleeps peacefully in his crate at night although he’d love to sleep in your bed! 
Ben is an adolescent dog and loves to "test the waters", and since it was difficult to curb his jumping he is in training classes with a former canine police officer and he is a star pupil.  Ben is very smart and wants to please.  He has no aggression but he loves to play hard. He will do best in a home where he will be exercised faithfully with quality playtime and great walks. He is not aggressive in any way with other dogs or people but he wishes they would play the way he does.  He loves the attention he gets from people on his walks and he is fine having the neighborhood kids ride their bikes and scooters along with him.
Ben has three more sessions with his trainer.  In the meantime he is happy in his foster home as he waits for his happily ever after.  He will be placed in a home with pitbull experience, someone who will keep him on track,  and where he'll get the exercise he craves so much. Ben is not suited for apartment or condo living. He requires a fenced yard to work off his youthful exuberance.
Ben is fostered in Barnegat, NJ and is neutered and up to date with vaccinations. An adoption within a 40 mile radius is preferred.
If you think your family dynamic is a good match for Benjamin, please complete an application at www.pounddogfounddog.org. Inquiries at Peggy_Kinahan@msn.com.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Gryphon is an American bully/ hound mix (born around 2/20/20) that came to us from a really rough situation. He was first posted on an Alabama lost and found site as found. It was discovered he had owners. Luckily animal control was able to get him out and safe. He was suffering from extreme demeodex mange. He was also quite thin and had badly infected eyes. The infection was so bad it resulted in loss of one of them. But as you can see, Gryphon has healed amazingly well. Gryphon absolutely loves his people; his foster mom says he is always near her or within eye sight. He also loves all dogs and kitties. Doesn't matter the size he plays with everyone. He can be a little rough and rowdy with his play so he will need a playmate that can tolerate a little wrestling and who likes to play chase.
He is housebroken and kennel trained, but his foster mom does admit that he sleeps in bed with her at night. He would not do well in an apartment as sometimes he can be a bit vocal. He also will require a privacy fence as he can easily jump or scale a chain link, especially if it means getting to his person.

Amazing Grace Bully Rescue is a foster based rescue in the Pensacola, Florida area. We do not have a physical building. If you would like to meet any of our pups, the first step is to fill out our online application so we can contact you.

Our adoption fee for Gryphon is $225and includes his neuter, current shots, rabies vaccine, and a registered microchip.

If you would like to adopt this Amazing dog, please fill out our online adoption application at www.amazinggracebullyrescue.org

If you have any questions, please text your question to 723-2037. You may also send a message to our Amazing Grace Bully Rescue Page on Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, or send an email directly to amazinggracebullyrescue@gmail.com

Disclaimer: We are located in the Pensacola, Florida area and will consider local applicants first, especially with puppies since we use a vet in the local area.

animal.description:
Hi There! My name is June and I'm a very sweet 2 1/2 year old 90 lb girl looking for a new forever home. My previous home had other dogs and I just did not do well with a crowd. I might be ok with another male large dog but honestly, I'd love to be the only "furchild" in the home.

 I love kids but I can get a little over playful and might knock down a small child. Kids over age 10 would be best. My foster mom has taught me lots of fun things to do while I've been with her family. I really love going for bike rides attached by my springer and I even got to do a little scooter racing last fall. She thinks I would be really good at skijoring and maybe pulling a sled too. 

My new home should be an active one as I have tons of energy to burn...you know the old saying....."a tired dog is a good dog!". Short car rides are lots of fun, but my tummy gets a little upset on really long rides. My new home should have a fenced yard for me to play in and keeping me from exploring without a human. I also require plenty of tummy rubs!

Note from the humans: June is being fostered at Few Steps From Home rescue and they will be handling her adoption. You can fill out a meet-n-greet application on their website   www.fewstepsfromhome.com or email them at:     dogrescue0146@gmail.com

animal.description:
*Please read the entire bio*

I know, I know, I'm the cutest little thing you've ever seen. But before you rush to apply to take me home, you must know a few things about me.

You see, I was a matted mess when K9 took me in, they gave me a warm bath and trimmed my fur of knots & matts to show off my cute face. I'm a young lady, and I'm a bit timid, but once I get used to you, I will do zooms for hours! I like my foster siblings, they give me confidence & someone to play with. I really don't like to be alone, I'll be your shadow wherever you go. I love going for walks, toys, car rides, toys, treats, toys, snuggling up next to you, & did I mention treats & food. If you give me treats, I will love you forever! I'm really a happy and energetic pup. I don't bark, but I loooooove to be the center of attention. So if you're looking for a loyal sidekick, then I'm the one for you!

PLEASE read the notes below from my foster mom:

MAJOR NOTE: Ismay will need to be groomed regularly (she gets very shaggy). However, she is TERRIFIED of clippers, she will need a sedative/anti-anxiety medication to help her as she gets used to it.

- Ismay really needs someone that is around. She does NOT like being left alone, she wants to be around someone.

- While she likes to be around people, she is still very skittish and unsure. She'll most times try to run away when you try to pet her. Requires patience as she learns she likes the pets and attention.

- She would do well in a house with another dog that is confident and playful as she is energetic.

- She absolutely does NOT enjoy being confined and cannot tolerate being in a crate as she has injured herself in the past while in one. She has been left free roam of our house for short periods of time and she has not torn up or damaged anything.

- She is the sweetest, goofy pup, she just needs someones that will be patient with her as she learns that humans are nice.

Ismay is a female Maltese/Havanese mix with est DOB of 08/12/19 and weighs approximately 12 pounds.

animal.description:
Barks and Meows Rescue introduces Taz. He is a Lab/Beagle mix. He weighs 59lbs and is 1 1/2 years old. Taz is not a tall dog. He was surrendered to a shelter from a gentleman that had a bunch of dogs, but the neighbors kept complaining so he signed over 5 of them to the shelter. He has a medium length hair coat. Taz is very sweet. He is timid when he meets new people so a quiet home would be best for him. He has been very good with the other dogs but prefers the female canines, in his foster home. Since he is on the cautious side, if there are children in the home they should be older than 12 years plus so as not to frighten him. We believe he has Beagle in him. He is food motivated but more lab characteristics than a hound. Once Taz knows you, he is very affectionate. He is not crated in his foster home as he has not been destructive. He sleeps on a doggy bed at night but we bet he would love to sleep on a bed with a family member if given the chance. He is really nice and quiet. He is very mature for his age. He eats well and is fed twice daily. Taz loves to play outside. We don't believe he was a house dog before as he was not housebroken when we got him. Now he loves to be cuddled up with his family watching TV and will go outside only if he has other dogs to keep him company or his family goes out at the same time. He will require a lot of leash work but he loves to go out so we believe it won't take long before he is walking nicely with his family. He has not been destructive in his foster home at all. He loves toys of all sorts. He rides quite well in the vehicle. The ideal home for Taz would be one where the family member or members are home a fair amount. Another female socialized dog that he can build his confidence from would work nicely. Older children 12 years plus would be fine. No cats for him as he has not been tested. Taz is neutered, up to date with vaccines, dewormed, and heartworm tested negative. A fully fenced yard and a Veterinarian History of Compliance is mandatory to apply for our Taz.
Visit barksandmeows.ca for an online application. Available to Ontario Residents only!!!

animal.description: This sweet ole gal is Babii (Baby). Babii was surrendered to us when her family that had her all of her life could no longer care for her. We would love nothing more than to find this senior girl a home to live her life out in, especially before the holidays. 2020 has not been kind to us. This includes Babii. She lost the only family she has ever known. We are very optimistic and hope that there is a special family willing to provide a nice stable, calm, warm and loving home for her. Sure, she has some medical issues that come with old age that a manager will be happy to explain to you. Once you meet hr you will agree that she is worth a little extra care. Babii gets a bit grumpy when you touch her backend so are requiring a home with much older children, 12 years and above. she will be fine sharing a home with a calm dog that respects her space and age, no rambunctious youngins! Babii would appreciate not having to go up any stairs, that comes with age. If you are looking to fill your home with the soulful eyes of a deserving dog then please ask to meet Babii today.

animal.description:
This gorgeous girl is Avery! She is a Great Pyrenees mix with the cutest tan spots, fluffy half tail and the softest coat. She adores people and would love nothing more than to have a family just love on her and give her all of the attention she deserves. She is about 5 years old and weighs about 70 lbs. She gets along with smaller more submissive dogs but can be afraid of larger dogs. We are guessing she formerly lived in a situation where she lived with dogs who did not treat her very nicely. She also needs a quieter home with no small children. She is the perfect companion for someone living alone or a retired couple in a quiet home. She is crate trained, gorgeous, sweet and looking for a family of her own!

Avery is in a foster home in CO. A meet and greet can be arranged with an approved application.  She is spayed, up to date on all shots, microchipped and her adoption fee is $250.  Avery has been treated for heartworms, so she will just need to stay on preventatives. If you would like to add this cutie to your family, please complete an application here-

https://www.tracyspawsrescue.org/adoption-application


Services our dogs receive prior to adoption:
Chagas Testing
Heartworm Testing (age appropriate)
Tick Illness Testing (age appropriate)
All age appropriate vaccines
Heartworm and flea/tick preventatives 
Spay/neuter surgery 
Microchip

animal.description:
Mack is an adorable dog with a classic Bulldog face. He was about to be euthanized at a high kill shelter in GA when Eleventh Hour Rescue stepped in to save his life. Upon arrival it was very apparent that the kennel was stressful for Mack. He is friendly with everyone he meets but he tends to get very over stimulated. When he gets so excited or stimulated around his people he can sometimes grab his leash and begin pulling it. He has been undergoing training for this behavior and has made great progress! Of course, any owner would have to keep up on him with this training, and one with training and breed experience would be preferred.

Mack is good with other dogs outside of the home, but would do best in a house without other animals and with no children, as he can't always control himself when he gets stimulated. Due to Mack's stimulation issues, he would do best with an adopter with a fenced in yard!

If you are interested in Mack, please fill out an application at EHRDOGS.ORG and be sure to mention MACK BAILEY!

animal.description:
Meet Bruno Mars

Bruno is a big love bug. He is a people pleaser and thrives on attention. He is a big lug that needs someone to spend some time with him and provide love, structure and  training. He sure tries hard to be the best-est boy. 


His story;
Bruno Mars was taken into our rescue when an elderly man reached out to us trying to get help for dogs he had taken in and could not afford to care for any more.
Unfortunately  Bruno was with 5 other unneutered males dogs. Too many dogs looking to be alpha dog.  Bruno was chained in an attempt to prevent dog fights. We were contacted and took him into our rescue.

Personality; people pleasure, lovely
Behavior; love bug
Dog Friendly- does well with other female dogs
Crate trained
neutered male
12 mo.
Heartworm neg


*****PLEASE READ*****
Our dogs are located in Texas, but available for transport with Project Freedom Ride (PFR).
PFR drop off locations: Mt.Vernon WA,  Seattle WA, Oregon City Oregon 

Adoption fee is $450 which includes spay/neuter, current vaccinations, a registered microchip, negative heartworm test, flea/tick/heartworm preventative, health certificate and includes transports
costs.

animal.description: Sandy = TONS of F-U-N! That's right, I'm a girl who knows how to have a good time and I'm hoping you do too. Playtime is the best time, dontcha think? Whether I'm running laps to burn off some energy, horsing around with my dog pals or just having a fun time with youit's all good to me, I love it all! But it's not all fun and games all the time - I do know some basic commands. And I'm a really sweet girl. Don't be surprised if I give you a kiss or twobut that's once we've gotten to know each other. I'm actually a bit shy when I first meet someone. It doesn't mean I don't want to be friends, I just like to take my time getting to know my humans - that's all. So if you're okay with that, I say we get to know each other so we get closer to all the fun we're going to have together. Sound like a good plan?

animal.description: Meet Jake, a handsome 4-year-old, 58-pound mixed-breed with penetrating blue eyes. He came to SFAS when his guardian could no longer care for him and is now ready to find another loving family to call his own. Here at the shelter, Jake is a little slow to warm up to new people but, once he gets to know you, he is a real sweetie. If you have another dog(s) at home please let the scheduler you will be bringing them along for a Meet n' Greet with Jake so that we can make sure everyone gets along well before going home Jake's adoption fee is $130. He is neutered and microchipped and has age-appropriate vaccinations. A licensing/microchip fee may apply. Interested in meeting with Jake or being added to his waitlist? Please call (505) 983-4309 x 1610 and leave a voicemail message that includes the DOG'S NAME, plus YOUR NAME and A PHONE NUMBER - OR e-mail this information to adoption@sfhumanesociety.org. A scheduler will call you back within 48 hours to confirm your request. SFAS offers a variety of excellent training classes, seminars and Trainer Talks led by animal behavior professionals. These are $50 off for animals adopted from any shelter or rescue group! Due to current COVID-19 restrictions, classes and talks are all presented virtually using Zoom. For course descriptions, schedules and registration, visit https://sfhumanesociety.org/our-programs/behavior-training/group-training-classes/ for classes and https://sfhumanesociety.org/our-programs/behavior-training/special-seminars-and-workshops/ for seminars and Trainer Talks.
